$MEIP got slammed last week when news of their proposed merger with Infinity came out, and then within 5 hours of the announcement a law firm announced an investigation into the merger. 

Mergers like this are confusing, complex, and have a lot of moving parts.  So guessing what is going to happen or is causing the stock price issues is hard. But what I notice on the price drop Thursday and Friday, is that the relative vol and accumulationdistribution shot upwards. Those indicate a big rise in “demand” just as the stock price was falling, which is counter to the typical Supply:Demand:Price relationship. 

So even though we have no idea what’s fundamentally causing this, the fact that forces big enough to be seen by the technicals were buying that dip is noteworthy, and I’ll be taking a chance on it next week. Maybe we can get @stompingllama to share some thoughts on the “why” behind this, and the threats? Do llamas like cookies? 🍪 Bullish

Friday SUCKED! 🤮 Inflation data made the whole news cycle turn to “what if there’s a recession?” If people continue to panic, where can you look? Inverse ETFs and ETNs were built as financial tools that allow someone to buy long, but which are short some part of the market. 

For example:
$FAZ shorts banking and finance
$YANG is short Chinese stocks
$FNGD is inverse FAANG
$HIBS is short the highest beta S&P stocks
$LABD shorts biotech

None of these is an investment (short term trades only!), they all come w/ a fee that, in essence, forces the ETF/ETN to trend towards $0 over time. Every few years they reverse split to rebalance. They are also built to be volatile, with leverages so that they outperform the sector they’re tied to.

It is HIGHLY recommended new traders READ THE PROSPECTUS (Google it) that details exactly how each inverse trades! But when the market is crashing, lots of traders find opportunities in these, notice the pic showing how GREEN these were on Friday 👀 Bullish

Before any and all “bullish expansions” the indicators start with the same signals. 

1) The grey and green arrows most recent signals will be upwards pointing (TTMScalper and Pearson’s Pivot Point) ✅
2) the bidders trying to get in will start to raise their bids to get in faster, which will make the price show up with blue upwards pointing “TTMTrend” arrows ✅
3) The Williams %R will go over -50 ✅
4) The MACD will be spreading in an upward direction ✅
5) the DPO will be above the mobility range in DPO_MOBO ✅
6) the RandomWalk will be red over green ✅

Bonus if any of the following are true:
1) the bollinger bands are squeezed and the TTMWave is over 0✅
2) there is a pattern of increasing accumulationdistribution during a recent downtrend ✅
3) there is a pattern of 3 or more consecutive days of increasing relative volume (sum of the bars, not the tallest bar) during a flat or downtrend ✅
4) there are large increases in relative volume during a downtrend ✅
